#class structure


So we have a tile and a board right?

TILE
  -FN's checkbomb
  -vars
    ->Bool ismine
    ->Int Row
    -> Int Col
    -> int NumBombNeighbors
    -> Numsides


    checkbomb (int x, int y)
    {
      if (tile(x,y).isbomb())
      {
        game over
      }
      else if (tile(x,y).isempty())
      {
        run checkbomb on neighbors
        reveal
      }
      else
      {
        reveal
      }
    }

    SUB REVEALED, gui elements
      -empty
      -numbered
    SUB UNREVEALED, gui elements
      -flag
      -nothing



